    "message_1": "Consider the Lotka-Volterra predator-prey model given by the following system of differential equations:\n\ndx/dt = 2x - xy\ndy/dt = -3y + xy\n\nwhere x and y represent the populations of prey and predator respectively. Set the initial conditions x(0) = 4 and y(0) = 1.\n\nFind the populations of prey and predator at time t = 2 using the forward Euler method with a time step of h = 0.2.",
