teration 8 (t = 1.6):\nx(1.6) = 0.701533264 + 0.2 * (2 * 0.701533264 - 0.701533264 * 5.139741536) = 0.701533264 + 0.2 * -2.7897088 = 0.15746744\ny(1.6) = 5.139741536 + 0.2 * (-3 * 5.139741536 + 0.701533264 * 5.139741536) = 5.139741536 + 0.2 * -12.418948864 = 2.667741536\n\nIteration 9 (t = 1.8):\nx(1.8) = 0.15746744 + 0.2 * (2 * 0.15746744 - 0.15746744 * 2.667741536) = 0.15746744 + 0.2 * -0.263274496 = 0.110052992\ny(1.8) = 2.667741536 + 0.2 * (-3 * 2.667741536 + 0.15746744 * 2.667741536) = 2.667741536 + 0.2 * -6.674216704 = 1.000741536\n\nIteration 10 (t = 2.0):\nx(2.0) = 0.110052992 + 0.2 * (2 * 0.110052992 - 0.110052992 * 1.000741536) = 0.110052992 + 0.2 * 0.109364464 = 0.132125888\ny(2.0) = 1.000741536 + 0.2 * (-3 * 1.000741536 + 0.110052992 * 1.000741536) = 1.000741536 + 0.2 * -2.890429184 = 0.421741536\n\nThus, at time t = 2, the population of prey x(2) is approximately 0.132 and the population of predator y(2) is approximately 0.422."
